<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-08T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/65</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-08T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your January 30, 6 p.m. Investigate and report fully to Department as to
                            legality of decree calling for constitutional election of deputies by
                            popular vote and legality of calling for constitutional convention to
                            assemble in May to form new Constitution to elect a President.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>